<h1>LG Washer Water Inlet Valve Replacement</h1>

<p>The water inlet valve controls how water enters your LG washer — when it fails, the washer either won't fill (an IE code) or won't stop filling (an FE overfill). Once we've ruled out a closed faucet or a clogged inlet screen, replacing the valve is a straightforward same-day fix. We do it across LA — $280–340 with a one-year warranty. Call (323) 990-7550.</p>

<h2>Signs Your Inlet Valve Has Failed</h2>
<p>A failing valve shows up one of two opposite ways. Stuck closed, the washer won't fill or fills very slowly — an <a href="/washer/symptoms/lg-washer-not-filling/">LG washer that won't fill</a>, usually with an <a href="/washer/error-codes/lg-washer-ie-error/">IE code</a>. Stuck open, it overfills and won't shut off, throwing an <a href="/washer/error-codes/lg-washer-fe-error/">FE overfill code</a>. Both come from the same part, so the direction of the fault tells us how the valve failed.</p>

<h2>How We Replace the Inlet Valve</h2>
<p>First our techs confirm the faucets are fully open and the mesh inlet screens are clear — a clogged screen or a half-shut tap mimics a failing valve and costs nothing to fix. If the valve is the cause, we test its solenoids, replace the valve assembly with an OEM part, and check the connections for leaks before testing a fill. It's about a 45–75 minute job.</p>

<h2>Cost of Inlet Valve Replacement</h2>
<p>Water inlet valve replacement runs $280–340 installed with an OEM valve, and the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair. For how this fits among other LG washer prices, see our <a href="/washer/price-list/lg-washer-repair-cost/">LG washer repair cost</a> page.</p>

<h2>Won't Fill vs Overfill</h2>
<p>It surprises people that the same valve causes both no-fill and overfill, but it's one part failing in opposite directions — stuck closed it starves the drum, stuck open it floods it. Either way the valve has lost control of the water, so we diagnose which fault you have and replace the valve to restore proper filling.</p>

<h2>OEM Parts and Warranty</h2>
<p>We fit OEM inlet valves, not generic units that can leak or fail early, and back the work with a one-year warranty on parts and labor. There's no surcharge for same-day or weekend service.</p>

<p>Washer sitting empty or overflowing? Our LG Dryer Repair techs test the supply and valve on-site across LA, Orange County, and Ventura County before quoting. Call (323) 990-7550; the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions — LG Washer Water Inlet Valve Replacement</h2>

<h3>How do I know if my LG washer water inlet valve is bad?</h3>
<p>A failing water inlet valve makes an LG washer either refuse to fill (often an IE code) or overfill because it won't shut off (an FE code). Both come from the same valve failing — stuck closed or stuck open — once the faucets and inlet screens are confirmed clear.</p>

<h3>How much does LG washer inlet valve replacement cost?</h3>
<p>Water inlet valve replacement runs $280–340 installed with an OEM valve. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair, and the work has a one-year warranty. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Could it be a clogged screen instead of the inlet valve?</h3>
<p>Yes, and we check that first — the small mesh screens where the hoses connect catch sediment and choke the fill, which mimics a failing valve. Cleaning the screens or opening a half-closed faucet costs only the service call; we only replace the valve when it's genuinely the valve.</p>

<h3>Why does my LG washer overfill — isn't that the opposite of not filling?</h3>
<p>It's the same part failing the other way. The inlet valve can stick closed (no fill, IE) or stick open (won't stop filling, FE). Either way the valve isn't controlling water properly and needs replacing, and we identify which fault you have before quoting.</p>

<h3>How long does LG washer inlet valve replacement take?</h3>
<p>An inlet valve replacement takes about 45–75 minutes, and we do it same-day in most cases. We test the fill and check for leaks before we leave.</p>

